description: The A5183 at Dunstable was closed on Monday while police investigated the fatal collision.
title: Man arrested after motorcyclist killed in Dunstable crash
title_page: Man arrested after motorcyclist killed in Dunstable crash - BBC News
maintext:
A man in his 40s has been arrested after a motorcyclist was killed in a crash on an A-road.
Bedfordshire Police was called shortly after 05:40 GMT to a collision between a car and a motorcycle in Dunstable.
The A5183 Watling Street has reopened after being closed for several hours.
Emergency services attended, but the rider, a man in his 20s, was pronounced dead at the scene.
